gomodel:SYNGO_278  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig 1. Cultured rat neurons at DIV 7 that overexpress a kinase-dead mutant of flag-tagged EphB2 (fEphB2_KD) form significantly less spines compared with WT EphB2 (fEphB2) and EphB2 lacking its PDZ domain (fEphB2deltaPDZ).\nFig. 3/4 fEphB2 expressed in heterologous cells co-cultured with neurons triggers in contacting axons clustering of presynaptic vesicles (SV2 staining) in synapses that are functional (FM4-64 uptake).\nFig 5. Knockdown of EphB2 in cultured cortical neurons results in decreased presynaptic puncta, spine number, and mEPSCs.\nFig 6. Synapse density as measured by immunohistochemistry in sections of cortex from early postnatal mice lacking EphB1, EphB2, and EphB3 is reduced.\nFig 7. EphB2 expression in cultured cortical sections of EphB1, 2, 3 KO mice is sufficient to rescue decreased PSD95 puncta on protrusions.. Experimental description: Dissociated cortical neurons were prepared from embryonic day 17 (E17) to E18 rats.\n\n11/10/2017 Pim\n- Species of EphB2 construct not stated in publication or referenced figures. Email sent for species information ( Matthew.Dalva@jefferson.edu; dalvalab@mail.med.upenn.edu, dd. 11/10/2017). Author answered:\n\"Dear Dr Nierop -\n\nThank you for your email. I am not familiar with your project (though I should be!). As someone very interested in the synapse and its organization I would love to learn more about what you are doing. \"\n\n- Mouse species is selected based on author feedback" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0912-1514" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3670-7863" ;
        dc:date           "2017-10-12" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_278" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

